'''Allu Aravind'''  {{Audio|alluaravind.ogg|pronunciation}} (born 10 January 1949) is an Indian [[film producer]] and distributor in [[Cinema of Andhra Pradesh|Tollywood]] and political candidate. He produces films under his production company [[Geetha Arts]] with his brother in law, Chiranjeevi.

He is an active member in the Prajarajyam Party founded by [[Chiranjeevi|Chiranjeevi Konidala]], he resigned as general secretary of PRP and later again became the general secretary for the party on a special request from party president Chiranjeevi.<ref>http://www.bharatwaves.com/news/article-14525.html</ref> Aravind has contested<ref>http://www.mpmla.in/mp.php?stcode=S01&pcno=6</ref> for MP from [[Anakapalli]].

Aravind is the son of [[Padmasri Allu Rama Lingaiah]]. He is the father of [[Allu Arjun]], who is also an actor, and [[Allu Sirish]], who made his debut with ''[[Gouravam (2013 film)|Gouravam]]'', under the direction of [[Radha Mohan]].<ref>http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=exYgWLzj0mw</ref> He is also the uncle of [[Ram Charan Teja]]. He has three sons named Allu Venkatesh, [[Allu Arjun]], and [[Allu Sirish]].

